#: ../../N/NMI.rst:5
msgid "NMI"
msgstr "NMI"

#: ../../N/NMI.rst:7
msgid "/N·M·I/, n\\."
msgstr "/N·M·I/, 名詞"

#: ../../N/NMI.rst:9
msgid ""
"Non-Maskable Interrupt. An IRQ 7 on the :ref:`PDP-11` or 680[01234]0; the "
"NMI line on an 80[1234]86. In contrast with a :ref:`priority-interrupt` "
"(which might be ignored, although that is unlikely), an NMI is *never* "
"ignored. Except, that is, on :ref:`clone` boxes, where NMI is often ignored "
"on the motherboard because flaky hardware can generate many spurious ones."
msgstr ""
"Non-Maskable Interrupt(マスク不能割り込み)。\\ :ref:`PDP-11`\\ や680[01234]0ではIRQ "
"7、80[1234]86ではNMI線にあたる。\\ :ref:`priority-interrupt`\\ "
"(無視されうる。可能性は低いが)とは対照的に、NMIは\\ *決して*\\ 無視されない。ただし\\ :ref:`clone`\\ "
"機は別で、そこではいい加減なハードウェアが多くの偽のNMIを生成しうるため、マザーボード上でNMIがしばしば無視される。"
